The paper discusses the problem of optimal signature-based IDS configuration under resource constraints, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves applying game theory concepts, such as Shapley value and Banzhaf-Coleman index, to quantify the influence or contribution of libraries in an IDS, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of knapsack optimization, which is a topic related to network optimization (cs.NI) and algorithms (cs.DS).
